<topic id="set-parameters-command-line-scripts">
  <title>Setting Parameters in the Command Line Scripts</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Startup parameter<indexterm>command line scripts
          parameters</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>OutOfMemory</indexterm>
        <indexterm>OutOfMemoryError</indexterm>
        <indexterm>Out Of Memory</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>If you start <ph keyref="product"/> with the <ph product="editor">
        <filepath>oxygen.bat</filepath>
      </ph>
      <ph product="author">
        <filepath>oxygenAuthor.bat</filepath>
      </ph>
      <ph product="developer">
        <filepath>oxygenDeveloper.bat</filepath>
      </ph>
      <ph product="diff"> </ph><ph product="diff"><filepath>diffFiles.bat</filepath>
      </ph>
      <ph product="svnClient">
        <filepath>syncroSVNClient.bat</filepath>
      </ph> script, you have to add or modify the parameter to the java command at the end of the
      script.</p>
    <p>For example, to set the maximum amount of Java memory to 600 MB on <b>Windows</b>, modify the
        <b>-Xmx</b> parameter like this: </p>
    <codeblock>java -Xmx600m -Dsun.java2d.noddraw=true ...</codeblock>
    <p product="editor author developer svnClient diff">on <b>Mac OS X</b> the java command should
      look like: </p>
    <codeblock product="editor" xml:space="preserve">java "-Xdock:name=Oxygen"\
 -Dcom.oxygenxml.editor.plugins.dir="$OXYGEN_HOME/plugins"\
 -Xmx600m\
 ...</codeblock>
    <codeblock product="author" xml:space="preserve">java "-Xdock:name=Author"\
 -Dcom.oxygenxml.editor.plugins.dir="$AUTHOR_HOME/plugins"\
 -Xmx600m\
 ...</codeblock>
    <codeblock product="developer" xml:space="preserve">java "-Xdock:name=Developer"\
 -Dcom.oxygenxml.editor.plugins.dir="$DEVELOPER_HOME/plugins"\
 -Xmx600m\
 ...</codeblock>
    <codeblock product="diff" xml:space="preserve">java "-Xdock:name=DiffFiles"\
 -Dcom.oxygenxml.editor.plugins.dir="$/OXYGEN_XML_DIFF_HOME/plugins"\
 -Xmx600m\
 ...</codeblock>
    <codeblock product="svnClient" xml:space="preserve">java "-Xdock:name=SyncroSVNClient"\
 -Xmx600m\
 ...</codeblock>
    <p>and on <b>Linux</b> the Java command should look like: </p>
    <codeblock><ph product="editor">java -Xmx600m\
 "-Dcom.oxygenxml.editor.plugins.dir=$OXYGEN_HOME/plugins"\</ph>
<ph product="author">java -Xmx600m\
 "-Dcom.oxygenxml.editor.plugins.dir=$AUTHOR_HOME/plugins"\</ph>
<ph product="developer">java -Xmx600m\
 "-Dcom.oxygenxml.editor.plugins.dir=$DEVELOPER_HOME/plugins"\</ph>
<ph product="diff">java -Xmx600m\
 "-Dcom.oxygenxml.editor.plugins.dir=$OXYGEN_XML_DIFF_HOME/plugins"\</ph>
<ph product="svnClient">java -Xmx600m\</ph></codeblock>
  </body>
